I'm vegetarian - so I skipped the beef. I used this puree as a dip and spread instead - and it's just wonderful. Everyone at the party loved it. The tarragon and nutmeg make this recipe special. I don't like mayonnaise, so I used half of the required amount and substituted the rest with sour cream - and as I said - excellent!

Rating: 4
I have made this several times. A quick substitute for the tenderloin is deli (high quality)london broil. The flavor is just as good. I made small piles of the london broil instead of slicing. I also grated the parmesan as a short cut that helped reduce preparation time. Very good! Don't skip the arugula...it makes it!

